1 (d) For timeshare estates located in this State, the managing entity shall have a lien on a
2 timeshare for any assessment levied against that timeshare from the date such assessment
3 becomes due. The managing entity shall also have a lien on a timeshare estate of any owner for
4 the cost of any maintenance, repairs, or replacement resulting from an act of the owner or the
5 owner's guest or lessee that results in damage to the timeshare property. All of the following
6 apply to a lien imposed under this section:
7 (1) The managing entity, or the holder of the lien, may bring a judicial action in
8 its name to foreclose the lien in the nature of an action to foreclose a mortgage
9 or deed of trust and may also bring an action to recover a money judgment for
10 the unpaid assessments without waiving any claim of lien. As an alternative
11 to initiating a judicial action, the managing entity entity, or the holder of the
12 lien, may initiate a nonjudicial timeshare trustee foreclosure proceeding
13 pursuant to G.S. 93A-62.1 to foreclose the assessment lien.
14 (2) The lien is effective from the date of and shall relate back to the recording of
15 the original timeshare declaration, or, in the case of lien on a timeshare located
16 in a phase timeshare program, the last to occur of the recording of the original
17 timeshare declaration or amendment creating the timeshare. However, as to
18 first mortgages of record, the lien is effective from and after filing of the claim
19 of lien in the office of the clerk of superior court in the county where the
20 timeshare estate is located.
21 (3) The claim of lien shall state the name of the timeshare program and identify
22 the timeshare for which the lien is effective, state the name of the owner, state
23 the assessment amount due, and state the due dates. The claim of lien shall be
24 signed and acknowledged by an officer or agent of the managing entity or the
25 holder.holder of the lien.
26 (4) The lien shall expire upon the earlier of:
27 a. The date it is satisfied.
28 b. Five years from the date the claim of lien is filed unless an action to
29 enforce or foreclose the lien is commenced within that time.
30 (5) A claim of lien for assessments may include assessments which are due when
31 the claim is recorded and all assessments that subsequently become due and
32 are delinquent. Upon full payment, the person making the payment is entitled
33 to receive a satisfaction of the lien.
34 (6) A judgment in any judicial action or suit brought to foreclose the claim of lien
35 may include costs and reasonable attorney's fees for the substantially
36 prevailing party. For a timeshare trustee foreclosure brought pursuant to this
37 section, the managing entity or the holder of the lien shall be entitled to
38 recover its costs, including reasonable attorney's fees and trustee's fees.
39 (e) A Except in the event of a timeshare trustee foreclosure conducted in accordance with
40 G.S. 93A-62.1, a successor in interest, regardless of how the timeshare has been acquired,
41 including a purchaser at a judicial sale or foreclosure trustee sale, is jointly and severally liable
42 with their predecessor in interest for all unpaid assessments against the predecessor up to the time
43 of transfer of the timeshare to a successor, without prejudice to any right a successor in interest
44 may have to recover from their predecessor in interest any amounts assessed against the
45 predecessor and paid by the successor; provided, however, a first mortgagee or its successor or
46 assignee who acquires title to a timeshare as a result of the foreclosure of the mortgage or by
47 deed in lieu of foreclosure of the mortgage shall be exempt from liability for all unpaid
48 assessments attributable to the timeshare or chargeable to the previous owner which came due
49 prior to acquisition of title by the first mortgagee. In the event of a timeshare trustee foreclosure,
50 owners who do not object to use of the timeshare trustee foreclosure procedure shall not be
51 subject to a deficiency judgment even if the proceeds from the sale of the timeshare are
