1 the notice, then the trustee shall have notice published in a newspaper in the
2 same manner as described in subsection (g) of this section.
3 (3) The notice of sale shall contain at least all of the following:
4 a. The name and address of the owner and any junior interest holders.
5 b. The legal description of the timeshare.
6 c. The name and address of the trustee.
7 d. A description of the default that is the basis for the judgment.
8 e. The filing information for the claim of lien and judgment.
9 f. The amounts secured by the lien and a per diem amount to account for
10 further accrual of the amounts secured by the lien.
11 g. The date, location, and starting time of the trustee's sale.
12 h. The right and method by which the owner may cure the default and the
13 right of any junior interest holder to redeem its interest up to the date
14 the trustee issues a certificate of sale in accordance with subdivision
15 (8) of this subsection.
16 (4) The trustee shall add to the amount of the judgment as costs of the sale any
17 postage or advertising expenses incurred by the managing entity, holder of the
18 lien, or designated trustee in foreclosing under this section.
19 (5) The managing entity, holder of the lien, and any other person other than the
20 trustee may bid at the sale. In lieu of participating in the sale, the lienholder
21 may send the trustee written bidding instructions that the trustee shall
22 announce as appropriate during the sale.
23 (6) The trustee may postpone the sale from time to time. In such case, notice of
24 postponement must be given by the trustee at the date, time, and location
25 contained in the notice of sale. The notice of postponed sale shall be given in
26 accordance with subdivision (2) of this subsection.
27 (7) The highest bidder at the sale shall pay the price bid to the trustee in cash or
28 certified funds on the day of the sale. If the managing entity or holder of the
29 lien is the highest bidder, the lienholder shall receive a credit up to the amount
30 set forth in the notice of sale, as described in subdivision (3) of this subsection.
31 (8) On the date of sale and upon receipt of the cash or certified funds due from
32 the highest bidder, the trustee shall issue to the highest bidder a certificate of
33 sale stating that a foreclosure conforming to the requirements of this section
34 has occurred. The certificate shall include the time, location, and date of the
35 sale, that the timeshare was sold, the amounts secured by the lien, and the
36 amount of the highest bid. A copy of the certificate shall be mailed by
37 first-class mail to the owner's address as recorded in the books and records of
38 the timeshare program. Upon issuance of a certificate of sale, all rights of
39 redemption are foreclosed and shall terminate.
40 (m) A sale conducted under this section releases the owner from liability for all amounts
41 secured by the lien. The managing entity or holder of the lien have no right to a deficiency
42 judgment against the owner after a sale of the owner's timeshare under this section.
43 (n) Within 10 calendar days after the trustee conducts a sale under this section, the trustee
44 shall execute and file with the clerk of superior court, a certificate of compliance that has been
45 signed and sworn to or affirmed before a notary public. In furtherance of the execution of the
46 certificate of compliance required under this subsection, the trustee is entitled to rely upon an
47 affidavit or certification from the managing entity or holder of the lien as to the facts and
48 circumstances of default and failure to cure the default. The certificate of compliance shall
49 contain the following:
50 (1) A confirmation of delivery of the claim of lien and notice of timeshare trustee
51 foreclosure.
