1 (2) A statement that the default was not cured prior to the sale, that the trustee did
2 not receive any written objection under subsection (f) of this section, and that
3 the timeshare was not redeemed under sub-subdivision h. of subdivision (1)
4 of subsection (l) of this section.
5 (3) A confirmation that the notice of sale was delivered to the owner or published
6 prior to the sale.
7 (o) At least 10 calendar days after a sale conducted under this section, absent the prior
8 filing and service on the trustee of a judicial action to enjoin issuance of the trustee's deed to the
9 highest bidder, the trustee shall issue a trustee's deed to the highest bidder and record the trustee's
10 deed in the public records of the county in which the timeshare is located. The trustee's deed shall
11 include the name and address of the trustee, the name and address of the highest bidder, the name
12 of the former owner, and a legal description of the timeshare. The trustee's deed shall contain no
13 warranties of title from the trustee. The trustee's deed conveys to the highest bidder all rights,
14 title, and interest in the timeshare that the former owner had, or had the power to convey, at the
15 time of the recording of the claim of lien, together with all rights, title, and interest that the former
16 owner or the owner's successors in interest acquired after the recording of the claim of lien.
17 (p) The trustee shall apply the proceeds of the sale as follows:
18 (1) To the expenses of the sale, including compensation of the trustee in
19 accordance with this section.
20 (2) To the amount owed and set forth in the notice of sale.
21 (3) If there are junior interest holders, the trustee may pay the surplus to the clerk
22 of superior court, naming the competing junior interest holders, and the
23 payment to the clerk discharges the managing entity, holder of the lien, or
24 trustee from liability to the extent of the amount paid. A special proceeding
25 may be instituted in accordance with G.S. 45-21.32 to determine who may be
26 entitled to the surplus.
27 (4) If there are no junior interest holders, or if all junior interest holders have been
28 paid, any surplus shall be paid to the former owner.
29 (q) The certificate of compliance and the trustee's deed together are presumptive evidence
30 of the truth of the matters set forth in them, and action to set aside the sale and void the trustee's
31 deed may not be filed or otherwise pursued against any person acquiring the timeshare interest
32 for value. The issuance and recording of the trustee's deed is presumed valid and may be relied
33 upon by third parties without actual knowledge of irregularities in the foreclosure proceedings.
34 If for any reason there is an irregularity in the foreclosure proceedings, a purchaser becomes
35 subrogated to all the rights of the lienholder to the indebtedness that it secured to the extent
36 necessary to re-foreclose the assessment lien in order to correct the irregularity and becomes
37 entitled to an action de novo for foreclosure of such assessment lien. Any subsequent
38 re-foreclosure required to correct an irregularity may be conducted under G.S. 93A-62.1.
39 (r) The managing entity, holder of the lien, or designated trustee may combine the claim
40 of lien, certificate, notice of sale, certificate of compliance, published notices and other
41 documents part of the timeshare trustee foreclosure procedure against timeshares of different
42 owners if both of the following criteria are met:
43 (1) All timeshares are part of the same timeshare project.
44 (2) The declaration giving rise to the right of the managing entity to collect
45 assessments creates default and remedy obligations that are substantially the
46 same for each owner named in the timeshare trustee foreclosure proceeding.
47 (s) A claim of lien securing a debt consisting solely of fines imposed by the managing
48 entity, interest on unpaid fines, or attorneys' fees incurred by the managing entity solely
49 associated with fines imposed by the managing entity may be enforced by judicial foreclosure,
50 as provided in Article 29A of Chapter 1 of the General Statutes. In addition, any claim of lien
51 securing a debt consisting solely of service, collection, consulting, or administration fees may
