1 only be enforced by judicial foreclosure, as provided in Article 29A of Chapter 1 of the General
2 Statutes.
3 (t) All foreclosure proceedings commenced by a managing entity or the holder of the
4 lien before October 1, 2025, and all sales and transfers of real property as part of those
5 proceedings pursuant to the provisions of this Chapter, Chapter 47A of the General Statutes, or
6 provisions contained in a timeshare declaration are declared to be valid unless an action to set
7 aside the foreclosure is commenced on or before October 1, 2025, or within one year after the
8 date of the foreclosure sale, whichever occurs last."
9 SECTION 3. This act is effective when it becomes law and applies to claims of lien
10 filed on or after that date.
